title: Hannibal Ending - 2x10 Naka-Choko
author: snatchingsouls
comment: One of the most aesthetically pleasing series of all time. Aesthetic - this is what this show was all about. Aesthetics which cross the boundaries of ethics. "I gave up good and evil for behaviorism".
Literally my first time watching this scene and my thought was how erotic it was. The eyesex here was strong!
That blur at the end is just *chef's kiss*👌🏾😃👥🫀 #savehannibal
Will was being really careful to be truthful here, so I was going to say I bet he just found a really long pig to feed Hannibal, but then I realised it was probably Randall they were eating.

Yes you are supposed to watch this show as hightend reality poetry rather than being completely literal and they care more about something feeling true in each individual moment rather than logical as a whole.
